# Reports/Finance — PBIP and delivery

## Source of truth

- **Editable projects:** use the real company PBIP folders under `Reports/Finance/Companies/<CODE>/` — do not guess a synthetic folder name.
- **Canonical current paths:**
  - `Reports/Finance/Companies/CANON/Canon Financial Report/Canon Financial Report.pbip`
  - `Reports/Finance/Companies/PAPERENTITY/Paper Financial Report/Paper Financial Report.pbip`
- **Development master:** **PBIP** only. **PBIX** = optional review/transfer snapshot; merge real changes back into PBIP.
- **Workflow:** edit the PBIP as source of truth, and follow the review/package guidance recorded in Finance `Project Memory` when the user needs an inspection artifact.

## Live memory (update after meaningful work)

- **Current state / handoff:** `Module/Project Memory/CURRENT_STATUS.md`, `NEXT_STEPS.md`
- **Durable direction:** `Module/Project Memory/DECISIONS.md`, `PROJECT_DNA.md`
- **Model caveats:** `Module/Project Memory/MODEL_NOTES.md`
- Do **not** use `README.md` or `Module/docs/` as a status log; keep them stable.

## Design and UX rules

- **Benchmark:** `Module/Design Benchmarks/Sample 2` unless `Project Memory` overrides.
- **Currency:** Iraqi dinar (IQD) presentation consistently; formatting affects layout, not only numbers.
- **Systems, not one-offs:** Top KPI row and left-rail slicers are **shared patterns** across pages — fix consistently.
- **Order:** logic first (bindings, measures, stale filters), styling second.
- **Desktop wins:** If the user approves layout in Desktop, treat that synced PBIP as the visual baseline over older JSON-only assumptions.

## GitHub

- Meaningful work can be tracked with **Issues** (see repo `.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`). Local `gh` may need re-auth; see `Module/docs/foundation.md`.
